<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-29T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="1014" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1014">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3427.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-29T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 28, 10 p.m. Informally inquire whether or not continuance of
                            Associated Press service can be arranged. Investigate the general policy
                            of the Mexican Government in this matter. In view of the conservatism of
                            Associated Press dispatches there appears to be no reason why their
                            service should be stopped.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>